00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:19,200
a previous chapter.
We had taken the example of a relatively hot

98
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:25,900
star, here at 15000K.
Now that we have learned about black bodies,

99
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:29,750
we see that a hot star
essentially radiates in the blue wavelengths.

100
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,710
That is what happens here.
We have an extremely steep spectrum in the

101
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:34,880
blue
and we have a continuous one, which is the

102
